reviews.text: A new specialty coffee shop and cafe in Taikoo Place, offers Japanese-style food, Western light food, and hand-drip coffee.  Barista and waitress are friendly but seemed a bit shy.  Difference between Latte, Cappuccino, Flat white?  Same restretto shots, just different volume of milk vs foam.  Cappuccino would have the strongest taste of coffee.

The little place provides only a few lunch choices but good quality. The price is reasonable for the quality but only allowing 50 min for lunch is a bit tough.  We couldn't even finish our coffee and we wete told time is up!!!  Also it was quite an anti-climax to have to choose between paying with Mileslife App or getting the coffee at a discounted price with the lunch set.  Otherwise it would have deserved another star.

Excellent eatery place served with lots of hearts.

Menu choices aren't many but are done very well. Coffee is served professionally.

The only reason why it isn't 5 stars is because of the very limited space and most men will find it a bit cramped but I guess, this isn't the owner's fault. Hong Kong property market doesn't allow any spacious restaurant unless you are a big conglomerate.
Great food quality. It seems like small quantity of food but you will definitely feed you well. The mix of food is great and very health. The coffee selection is also wide and good quality.
Good is in good quality just a bit over price
